An Ado-Ekiti Customary Court in Ekiti State has dissolved an 11-year-old marriage between one Eunice Ajewole and her husband, Sanni Ajewole. Both parties had earlier in the year given their separate evidence while the case was adjourned. The court dissolved their marriage on the ground that Sanni deserted his wife, Eunice, for nine years while she was sick. During the hearing, Eunice told the court that she got married to her husband in 2009, under the native custom. She stated that their marriage was not blessed with any child. She added that she was always falling sick anytime she was with her husband, but that she would get well again immediately she was away from him. According to her, whenever she returned to her husband’s house, the sickness would resurface, adding that she had discovered that they were not compatible. Raufu Olaniyan: A true Omoluabi @ 60 The Ekiti State six-month  maternity leave Ayade and the dreams of our founding fathers Tech-U VC warns students against cultism, exam malpractice The petitioner, therefore, urged the court to dissolve the union between them. Also, the respondent, Sanni, 39, admitted that they were not compatible. He said immediately after their marriage, his wife fell ill and that anytime she was away from him, she would be well. Sanni who stated that he didn’t know the cause of the sickness added that this had become too frequent and he did not want her to die in his house. Sanni, therefore, supported the dissolution of their marriage. The court president, Mrs Olayinka Akomolede, observed that their marriage had broken down irretrievably and consequently dissolved it. Akomolede ruled that since there was no child between them, both parties should go their separate ways. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS